---
title: Deploy Redis
---

From the Mega Jumpbox, upload the releases and stemcell for the Redis installation:

```
bosh -n upload release /opt/artifacts/releases/cf-redis-346.4.tgz --skip-if-exists
bosh -n upload stemcell /opt/artifacts/stemcells/bosh-stemcell-3094-aws-xen-ubuntu-trusty-go_agent.tgz --skip-if-exists
```

- [ ] Modify the [Redis Deployment Manifest](https://github.com/pivotal-federal-field-engineering/dark-chiron-aws/tree/master/deployments/p-redis-chiron.yml "Manifest"): p-redis-chiron.yml in the deployments directory on the Mega Jumpbox to suit the environment.

Configure the following parameters as necessary:
* Director UUID (using <bosh status> above)
* Network Cloud Properties, Subnet-ID: (pcf-private-subnet, AWS Console: VPC)
* System domain: chiron.vi-works.io 
* Host: redis-broker.chiron.vi-works.io
* API URL: https://api.chiron.vi-works.io

- [ ] Set deployment:

```
bosh -n deployment /home/ubuntu/workspace/dark-chiron-aws/deployments/p-redis-chiron.yml
```

- [ ] Deploy Redis:

```
bosh -n deploy
```

- [ ] Run bosh utilities to confirm successful deployment:

```
bosh -n vms p-redis-chiron
bosh -n cck --report
```

- [ ] Run bosh errands to install Redis:

```
bosh -n run errand broker-registrar
```